PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Genuine Parts Co.'s GPC third-quarter earnings rose 15% as the automotive business continued to drive the replacement-parts provider's revenue growth. The operator of the NAPA auto-parts chain weathered the economic downturn relatively well as consumers turned to fixing old vehicles rather than buying new ones. The company has also seen increased profits in recent quarters as the manufacturing sector bounces back from recessionary woes. Genuine Parts reported a profit of $151.8 million, or 97 cents a share, up from $131.8 million, or 83 cents, a year earlier.

Headlines.Author: Barbara Kollmeyer
Headlines.Headline: BEFORE THE BELL: US Stock Futures Down On Mideast Violence

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Barbara Kollmeyer U.S. stock futures fell Tuesday, with Wall Street returning to action on a day of unrest for global markets as violence increased in the major oil-producing state of Libya, with the session also marked by corporate results from Wal-Mart Stores and Home Depot. Futures pared earlier losses, but they were still sharply lower. Futures for the Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 83 points, or 0.7%, to 12292, while those for the S&P 500 index fell 15.60 points, or 1.2%, to 1326.80. Futures for the Nasdaq 100 fell 31 points, or 1.5%, to 2364.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: BEFORE THE BELL: US Stock Futures Down On Mideast Violence

Headlines.Author: Barbara Kollmeyer
Headlines.Headline: BEFORE THE BELL:US Stock Futures Drop Sharply On Libya Concerns

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Barbara Kollmeyer U.S. stock futures dropped sharply on Tuesday, with Wall Street returning to action on a day of unrest for global markets as violence increased in the major oil-producing state of Libya. Futures for the Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 112 points, or 1%, to 12263, while those for the S&P 500 index fell 18.7 points, or 1.5%, to 1323.70. Futures for the Nasdaq 100 fell 36.5 points, or 1.6%, to 2358.50. U.S. markets were closed on Monday for the Presidents Day holiday. The Dow Jones Industrial Average marked its highest close since June 5, 2008, on Friday, with multiyear closing highs for the Nasdaq 100 index and S&P 500 as well.

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Genuine Parts Co.'s GPC third-quarter profit jumped a bigger-than-expected 22% as its auto and industrial businesses' sales continued to improve. The operator of the NAPA automotive parts chain has seen results improve this year, helped by a recovering manufacturing sector that Chairman and Chief Executive Thomas Gallagher said Friday "is performing well today." Headlines.Headline: Genuine Parts 4Q Net Slips 30% Amid Drop In Demand

#text: Genuine Parts Co.'s

fourth-quarter net income slipped 30% as weak consumer spending and a decline in industrial production hurt sales. Analysts were hopeful that retailers like Genuine Parts would be somewhat insulated from the recession as consumers opt out of buying new cars and instead attend to vehicle maintenance concerns. But Genuine Parts, which operates the National Automotive Parts Associated brand retail stores, posted net income of $87.8 million, or 55 cents a share, down from $126.1 million, or 75 cents a share.

Headlines.Author: Dow Jones
Headlines.Headline: Genuine Parts Co. Cuts Profit Outlook, Shares Fall

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Dow Jones NEW YORK (Dow Jones) -- Genuine Parts Co. saw its shares fall in early trade Friday after the auto-components distributor warned its full-year results will fall short of its previous forecast. The Atlanta-based company now expects 2008 sales growth of about 2% and earnings of $2.85 to $2.90 a share, including a 7-cent charge for the lower investment value in the company's retirement plan. Its prior outlook was for 3% sales growth and earnings of $3.12 to $3.18 a share. On average, analysts polled by FactSet Research were expecting full-year earnings of $3.11 a share.

#text: By Shawn Langlois SAN FRANCISCO (Dow Jones) -- Genuine Parts Co. on Thursday reported a higher first-quarter profit on the back of strong demand for the company's electrical products. Shares in Genuine Parts

have fallen almost 10% so far this year, but managed a slight uptick to finish at $42.13.
